description: Adds one or more users to a Users dataset. For more information see Importing users individually.

parameters.name: datasetArn
parameters.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Users dataset you are adding the user or users to.

parameters.name: users
parameters.description: A list of user data. (dict) --- Represents user metadata added to a Users dataset using the PutUsers API. For more information see Importing users individually. The ID associated with the user. properties (string) --- A string map of user-specific metadata. Each element in the map consists of a key-value pair. For example, {"numberOfVideosWatched": "45"}. The keys use camel case names that match the fields in the schema for the Users dataset. In the previous example, the numberOfVideosWatched matches the --NUMBER_OF_VIDEOS_WATCHED' field defined in the Users schema. For categorical string data, to include multiple categories for a single user, separate each category with a pipe separator ( |). For example, \"Member|Frequent shopper\".

nested_params.name: userId
nested_params.description: The ID associated with the user.
